title: MONDAY - Week 13 recap 2020
itunes:title: MONDAY - Week 13 recap 2020
description:
The Chiefs (0:06)become the first team in the AFC to clinch a playoff spot with their win over the Broncos. Patrick Mahomes talks about getting the victory (0:27). Meanwhile, the Saints locking up a playoff birth (2:11) with the win against the Falcons. Taysom Hill now 3-0 as the Saints starter (2:24). The Giants pull off the upset over the Seahawks (2:46) while the Rams take over first place in the NFC West with the win over the Cardinals (3:43), but Rams head coach Sean McVay not overly impressed (3:59). Plus the Browns (4:30), led by Baker Mayfield move to 9-3 with the big win over the Titans
